          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and recitation and is a post-Vedic upaniṣad, a philosophical treatise written in verse containing mantras and told through a narrative/mythological allegory, focusing on the centrality of the Hindu god Śiva as the highest principle in the universe and identifying him with the gods Viṣṇu, Brahmā, and Indra. The manuscript identifies itself as deriving from the Atharvaveda (f. 4v).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Kaivalyopaniṣad</title>
              <title type="vernacular">कैवल्योपनिषद्</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti atharvavede kaivalyopaniṣadsamāptaḥ // (f. 4v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
